    "source_commit": "8fec14c",
    "notes": [
      "Three-player JS oracle canary for active PrintManager.stop side effects after a body-collision death.",
      "p0 starts printing with an active PrintManager and overlaps a seeded p1 AvatarBody while p1 and p2 survive so the round does not end.",
      "The collision happens after Avatar.update and before PrintManager.test, so the manager is stopped by Avatar.die instead of updating distance or lastX/lastY.",
      "Avatar.die emits the normal non-important death point before PrintManager.stop emits the important stop point and printing=false property.",
      "The p0 trail cursor starts at the collision point to keep Avatar.update from adding a normal trail point before the body collision."
    ]
  },
